.TH "IDBCursor.advance" "JS" "March 6, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
IDBCursor.advance \- IDBCursor: advance() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]advance()\f[B]\f[R] method of the \f[CR]IDBCursor\f[R]
interface sets the number of times a cursor should move its position
forward.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
advance(count)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]count\f[R]
The number of times to move the cursor forward.
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SS Exceptions
This method may raise a \f[CR]DOMException\f[R] of one of the following
types:
.TP
\f[B]TransactionInactiveError\f[R] \f[B]DOMException\f[R]
Thrown if this IDBCursor\[cq]s transaction is inactive.
.TP
\f[B]TypeError\f[R]
Thrown if the value passed into the \f[CR]count\f[R] parameter was zero
or a negative number.
.TP
\f[B]InvalidStateError\f[R] \f[B]DOMException\f[R]
Thrown if the cursor is currently being iterated or has iterated past
its end.
.SH EXAMPLES
In this simple fragment we create a transaction, retrieve an object
store, then use a cursor to iterate through the records in the object
store.
Here we use \f[CR]cursor.advance(2)\f[R] to jump 2 places forward each
time, meaning that only every other result will be displayed.
\f[CR]advance()\f[R] works in a similar way to
\f[CR]IDBCursor.continue\f[R], except that it allows you to jump
multiple records at a time, not just always go onto the next record.
.PP
Note that in each iteration of the loop, you can grab data from the
current record under the cursor object using
\f[CR]cursor.value.foo\f[R].
For a complete working example, see our \c
.UR https://github.com/mdn/dom-examples/tree/main/indexeddb-examples/idbcursor
IDBCursor example
.UE \c
\ (\c
.UR https://mdn.github.io/dom-examples/indexeddb-examples/idbcursor/
View the example live
.UE \c
).
.IP
.EX
\f[B]function\f[R] advanceResult() {
  list.textContent = \[dq]\[dq];
  \f[B]const\f[R] transaction = db.transaction([\[dq]rushAlbumList\[dq]], \[dq]readonly\[dq]);
  \f[B]const\f[R] objectStore = transaction.objectStore(\[dq]rushAlbumList\[dq]);

  objectStore.openCursor().onsuccess = (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
    \f[B]const\f[R] cursor = event.target.result;
    \f[B]if\f[R] (cursor) {
      \f[B]const\f[R] listItem = document.createElement(\[dq]li\[dq]);
      listItem.textContent = \[ga]${cursor.value.albumTitle}, ${cursor.value.year}\[ga];
      list.appendChild(listItem);
      cursor.advance(2);
    } \f[B]else\f[R] {
      console.log(\[dq]Every other entry displayed.\[dq]);
    }
  };
}
.EE
